[{"data":1,"prerenderedAt":294},["ShallowReactive",2],{"header-locale:\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2021\u002F10\u002F13\u002Fhow-to-find-your-discord-id\u002F":3,"page:\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2021\u002F10\u002F13\u002Fhow-to-find-your-discord-id\u002F":4,"alt:\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2021\u002F10\u002F13\u002Fhow-to-find-your-discord-id\u002F":3,"prev-next:\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2021\u002F10\u002F13\u002Fhow-to-find-your-discord-id\u002F":269,"related:\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2021\u002F10\u002F13\u002Fhow-to-find-your-discord-id\u002F":278},"\u002Fother\u002F20211013\u002F4225269670\u002F",{"id":5,"title":6,"abbrlink":7,"altUrl":3,"body":8,"category":251,"date":252,"description":253,"extension":254,"lang":255,"meta":256,"navigation":257,"path":258,"readingMinutes":259,"seo":260,"standalone":261,"stem":262,"tags":263,"tldr":265,"updated":266,"url":267,"__hash__":268},"content\u002Fen\u002FMisc\u002Fhow-to-find-your-discord-id.md","How to Find Your Discord ID (Desktop + Mobile)","5520692674",{"type":9,"value":10,"toc":239},"minimark",[11,22,27,30,34,41,49,53,56,63,70,73,99,102,106,109,114,121,126,137,142,157,162,166,169,174,180,185,191,197,203,206,212,218,224,230,236],[12,13,14],"blockquote",{},[15,16,17,21],"p",{},[18,19,20],"strong",{},"Note","\nYour Discord ID is the unique numeric identifier for your account — a string of digits that never changes. To find yours, turn on Developer Mode in User Settings → Advanced, then click the \"⋯\" next to your avatar in My Account and pick \"Copy User ID\".",[23,24,26],"h2",{"id":25},"intro","Intro",[15,28,29],{},"I was building a Discord Bot recently and noticed something kind of annoying: Discord makes it weirdly fiddly to find your own User ID, and a lot of people end up grabbing the wrong thing. So this post walks through how to actually get it, with the mobile flow included.",[23,31,33],{"id":32},"whats-a-discord-id","What's a Discord ID?",[15,35,36,37,40],{},"First, let's sort out what a Discord ID actually is. Basically, your Discord ID is the ",[18,38,39],{},"unique identifier"," for your account. It never changes — which is why some services and bots will ask you to fill it in.",[15,42,43,44,48],{},"It's a long string of digits. Mine, for example, is ",[45,46,47],"code",{},"300879849289940992"," — that's my Discord ID.",[23,50,52],{"id":51},"the-wrong-things-people-grab","The wrong things people grab",[15,54,55],{},"If you're new to Discord, you might think the two highlighted bits below are your User ID (the arrows show what I mean):",[15,57,58],{},[59,60],"img",{"alt":61,"src":62},"User info","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002Fblog\u002Fother\u002Fdiscord-id\u002F20250426203841.png",[15,64,65,66,69],{},"That string \"",[18,67,68],{},"isray_notarray","\" isn't your Discord ID — it's just your username.",[15,71,72],{},"Discord actually has three different things going on here:",[74,75,76,87,93],"ul",{},[77,78,79,82,83,86],"li",{},[18,80,81],{},"Display Name",": This is the name shown to other people on Discord. Mine is set to \"",[45,84,85],{},"Ray ®","\", so that's what shows up.",[77,88,89,92],{},[18,90,91],{},"Username",": A handle you use to log in or be tagged. It's editable, so it's not a reliable identifier.",[77,94,95,98],{},[18,96,97],{},"User ID",": The unique identifier for your account — never changes, which is what services usually want.",[15,100,101],{},"So next we'll go through how to actually get the User ID — first on desktop, then on mobile.",[23,103,105],{"id":104},"turning-on-developer-mode","Turning on Developer Mode",[15,107,108],{},"Whether you're on desktop or mobile, step one is the same: turn on Developer Mode. This unlocks some extra info in the UI, like the option to copy User IDs and Channel IDs.",[110,111,113],"h3",{"id":112},"desktop","Desktop",[15,115,116,117,120],{},"Click \"",[18,118,119],{},"User Settings","\" at the bottom of the sidebar to open settings:",[15,122,123],{},[59,124],{"alt":119,"src":125},"https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002Fblog\u002Fother\u002Fdiscord-id\u002F20250426204558.png",[15,127,128,129,132,133,136],{},"In the left sidebar, find \"",[18,130,131],{},"Advanced","\" and toggle on \"",[18,134,135],{},"Developer Mode","\":",[15,138,139],{},[59,140],{"alt":135,"src":141},"https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002Fblog\u002Fother\u002Fdiscord-id\u002F20250426204726.png",[15,143,144,145,148,149,152,153,156],{},"Now go back to \"",[18,146,147],{},"My Account","\". You'll see a \"",[18,150,151],{},"⋯","\" next to your name — click it, and \"",[18,154,155],{},"Copy User ID","\" shows up. Click it and your User ID is on your clipboard.",[15,158,159],{},[59,160],{"alt":155,"src":161},"https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002Fblog\u002Fother\u002Fdiscord-id\u002F20250426205018.png",[110,163,165],{"id":164},"mobile","Mobile",[15,167,168],{},"The mobile flow also needs Developer Mode on. I'll use iOS as the example, but Android should be basically the same.",[15,170,171,172,136],{},"Open the app, tap your avatar in the bottom nav to open \"",[18,173,119],{},[15,175,176],{},[59,177],{"alt":178,"src":179},"Mobile User Settings","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002Fblog\u002Fother\u002Fdiscord-id\u002FIMG_8658.jpg",[15,181,182,183,136],{},"Scroll down and find \"",[18,184,131],{},[15,186,187],{},[59,188],{"alt":189,"src":190},"Mobile Advanced","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002Fblog\u002Fother\u002Fdiscord-id\u002FIMG_8660.PNG",[15,192,193,194,196],{},"Toggle \"",[18,195,135],{},"\" on:",[15,198,199],{},[59,200],{"alt":201,"src":202},"Mobile Developer Mode","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002Fblog\u002Fother\u002Fdiscord-id\u002FIMG_8661.PNG",[15,204,205],{},"Now go into any channel and send a message:",[15,207,208],{},[59,209],{"alt":210,"src":211},"Mobile send message","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002Fblog\u002Fother\u002Fdiscord-id\u002FIMG_8662.jpg",[15,213,214,215,136],{},"Tap your own avatar — a menu pops up. Tap \"",[18,216,217],{},"...",[15,219,220],{},[59,221],{"alt":222,"src":223},"Mobile menu","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002Fblog\u002Fother\u002Fdiscord-id\u002FIMG_8663.PNG",[15,225,226,227,229],{},"And \"",[18,228,155],{},"\" shows up. Tap it and the ID is copied:",[15,231,232],{},[59,233],{"alt":234,"src":235},"Mobile Copy User ID","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002Fblog\u002Fother\u002Fdiscord-id\u002FIMG_8664.PNG",[15,237,238],{},"That's how to find your Discord ID. Hope it helps.",{"title":240,"searchDepth":241,"depth":241,"links":242},"",2,[243,244,245,246],{"id":25,"depth":241,"text":26},{"id":32,"depth":241,"text":33},{"id":51,"depth":241,"text":52},{"id":104,"depth":241,"text":105,"children":247},[248,250],{"id":112,"depth":249,"text":113},3,{"id":164,"depth":249,"text":165},"Misc","2021-10-13 13:12:46","I was building a Discord Bot recently and noticed that finding your own Discord User ID is weirdly fiddly — and a lot of people get the wrong thing. So this post walks through how to grab it correctly, including the mobile flow.","md","en",{},true,"\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002Fhow-to-find-your-discord-id","2",{"title":6,"description":253},false,"en\u002FMisc\u002Fhow-to-find-your-discord-id",[264,135,165],"Discord",null,"2026-05-12 09:00:00","\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2021\u002F10\u002F13\u002Fhow-to-find-your-discord-id\u002F","eY26xZOhUGMBREtDgF_nJmcSFaxG7eE0u_R4dGEfCjo",{"newer":270,"older":274},{"url":271,"title":272,"date":273},"\u002Fen\u002Fnuxt\u002F2021\u002F10\u002F22\u002Fnuxt-2x-handbook-02-architecture-overview\u002F","Nuxt.js 2.x Hands-On Handbook (2) — Architecture Overview","2021-10-22 21:11:08",{"url":275,"title":276,"date":277},"\u002Fen\u002Fnuxt\u002F2021\u002F10\u002F11\u002Fnuxt-2x-handbook-01-intro-and-setup\u002F","Nuxt.js 2.x Hands-On Handbook (1) — Nuxt.js & Setup","2021-10-11 16:16:35",[279,284,289],{"url":280,"title":281,"date":282,"readingMinutes":283},"\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2026\u002F06\u002F23\u002Fmac-stats-menu-bar-system-monitor\u002F","Stats — The Free Open-Source macOS Menu Bar System Monitor I Use Every Day (CPU, GPU, Temperature, Network)","2026-06-23 10:00:00","5",{"url":285,"title":286,"date":287,"readingMinutes":288},"\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2026\u002F05\u002F26\u002Fhow-much-does-a-blog-really-earn-with-google-adsense\u002F","Can a Blog Really Make Tens of Thousands of Dollars a Month? Real Google AdSense Numbers, Explained","2026-05-26 21:00:00","6",{"url":290,"title":291,"date":292,"readingMinutes":293},"\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2026\u002F05\u002F18\u002Fvscode-disable-integrated-browser-auto-open\u002F","VSCode Opens Every Link in the Integrated Browser? How to Disable Auto Takeover","2026-05-18 14:30:00","4",1784011705230]